
---


@startuml

' Define actors
actor "Visitor" as Visitor
actor "Registered User" as RegisteredUser
actor "Administrator" as Admin
actor "System" as System

' Generalization of actors
RegisteredUser <|-- Visitor
Admin <|-- RegisteredUser

' Use Cases
usecase "Register Account" as UC_Register
usecase "Login" as UC_Login
usecase "Create Building" as UC_CreateBuilding
usecase "Add Entry to Building" as UC_AddEntry
usecase "Release Entry Publicly" as UC_ReleaseEntry
usecase "Search Buildings" as UC_Search
usecase "Comment on Building" as UC_Comment
usecase "Delete Comment" as UC_DeleteComment
usecase "Manage Users" as UC_ManageUsers
usecase "Setup User Account" as UC_SetupUserAccount

' Relationships between actors and use cases
RegisteredUser --> UC_Register
RegisteredUser --> UC_Login
RegisteredUser --> UC_CreateBuilding
RegisteredUser --> UC_AddEntry
RegisteredUser --> UC_ReleaseEntry
RegisteredUser --> UC_Comment
Visitor --> UC_Search
Admin --> UC_DeleteComment
Admin --> UC_ManageUsers
System --> UC_SetupUserAccount

' Class diagram

class WebPortal {
  - version: String
  - url: String
}

class Building {
  - id: String
  - name: String
  - energyClass: String
  - address: String
  - yearOfConstruction: int
  + setOwner(User)
}

class User {
  - username: String
  - email: String
  - password: String
  - activated: boolean
  + activate()
}

class Administrator extends User {
  - idCardNumber: String
}

class Entry {
  - name: String
  # isPublic: boolean
}

class TextualEntry extends Entry {
  - content: String
}

class NumericEntry extends Entry {
  - value: float
  - unit: String
}

class Image {
  - filename: String
  - isProfilePhoto: boolean
}

class Comment {
  - text: String
  - timestamp: DateTime
}

' Associations
WebPortal "1" --> "many" User : hosts
WebPortal "1" --> "many" Building : provides
Building "1" --> "many" Entry : contains
Building "1" --> "many" Image : has
Building "1" --> "1" User : owner
User "1" --> "many" Building : owns
User "1" --> "many" Comment : writes
Entry "1" --> "1" User : createdBy
Comment "1" --> "1" Building : belongsTo
Comment "1" --> "1" User : writtenBy

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation

- **Actors**:
  - `Visitor`: Can search buildings.
  - `Registered User`: Can register, login, create buildings, add entries, release entries publicly, comment.
  - `Administrator`: Special user who can manage users and delete comments.
  - `System`: Handles automatic setup and confirmation processes.

- **Use Cases**:
  - Includes 10 key use cases covering registration, searching, commenting, building management, entry management, and admin functions.

- **Generalization**:
  - `RegisteredUser` inherits from `Visitor`.
  - `Admin` inherits from `RegisteredUser`.

- **Classes & Relationships**:
  - `WebPortal` holds users and buildings.
  - Each `Building` has an owner and multiple entries and images.
  - `Entry` is abstract and has two subtypes: `TextualEntry` and `NumericEntry`.
  - `Comment` is linked to both `User` and `Building`.

